                <p> In today’s fast-paced world, it has become increasingly important to save time on travel and long waits and even longer delays in trains, buses or ships are no longer acceptable to many. This means that more and more people turn to air travel as a means of transportation from one location to another, especially for work and business-related trips. </p>

                <p> Air travel is the fastest and most effective way of travel. It has multiple advantages over other traditional methods of transportation. These include plus points such as routes of aircraft being unaffected by many natural disasters such as landslides and earthquakes, the tightening of security measures and a growing number of airports all over the world. </p>

                <p> Despite all this, the greatest disadvantage of air travel remains the high costs it charges its customers. Flight tickets all over the world remain significantly more costly than their rail, road or water counterparts. Reasons for this are many and varied including the high level of skill required from both pilots and cabin crew and exorbitant fuel rates. </p>

                <p> As a result of this, many companies from all corners of the world have started attempts to reduce the cost incurred on flight tickets. This has been proven to have the desired result of making air travel more accessible to people from all walks of life. Here are some tricks and tips from seasoned travellers to help keep your air travel within your budget. </p>

                <h2>Top 10 ways to get the cheapest flight tickets</h2>


                <ol>
                    <li>The methods to get cheaper tickets must be applied at the inception. Plan your trip carefully before you try to buy tickets. It is imperative that you have a flexible schedule while being sure of what you are looking for. </li>
                    <li>Make sure to plan your trip during the low season of your destination. If it is not possible to visit during the low season or there are certain attractions that you risk missing during that season opt for the shoulder seasons instead. </li>
                    <li>Avoid getting tickets during the peak season at all costs. If the timing of your trip needs to be fixed during that season, look for tickets as early as possible to make sure you do not miss out on any deals. </li>
                    <li>Look for the cheapest deals available. If you visit during the low season you are sure to find special deals meant to incentivise travel during that season. Festivals and holidays also provide lucrative deals intended as a celebration. </li>
                    <li>Try special features on the official websites of airlines which are meant to find the best deals available for you during that time at your location. </li>
                    <li>You can also opt for the assistance of websites which specialize in finding cheap deals and discounts for travellers. The <a href="https://www.faresmatch.com">FaresMatch</a> website is an example of such a travel website. </li>
                    <li>The cheapest tickets are generally available for the economy class. So, opting for the economy class or premium economy class is a good tactic especially if you have a short flight where comfort does not matter much. </li>
                    <li>Travellers should also choose direct flights without any stops as often as possible as these are generally the cheapest flights available to any location. </li>
                    <li>Travellers should avoid carrying any extra baggage as they might incur extra baggage fees. Pack lightly and only bring the necessary items with you.</li>
                    <li>Opting for low-cost airlines is a good idea as these airlines provide the cheapest flights to any destination and are specially designed for budget-conscious travellers.</li>
                </ol>
